snippet.textDisplay:
hey, i just have a critique id like to share- just genuine feedback

for the most part i just feel the camera is a bit too far out, and bowlbo is very tiny on screen-


the opening town where he hops over the couple he is incredibly tiny and i feel like im looking at the landscape more

"quack me up" was perfect in terms of the camera thing i mentioned, the car smash and the tree slap again he seemed very small, him running from the bull monster is actually ok with it being smaller, it feels like hes actually running from something large- camera coming into good play there

when hes in that red room with the pitchforks in the ground, it's alot better, only thing is the camera is kinda too far behind him, i think he should be more focused in center left, to see whats ahead, and as it is i can see more whats behind him as oppose in front (and i would say we can see a little too much above him, but it looks like for that specific level that's a necessity- given all the stuff happening above, so in that case that's all good)

downhill snow level again pretty tiny, tree-monster-thing rising up was perfectly fine like the bull

him talking to the lady again was too far out, and im focusing more on the house, and he looks tiny in that shot- funny enough i feel the woman is the size he should be, she looks good in that shot

all in all it looks cool, it's funny, i love the renders, the dark fantasy vibes, the clay art lookin direction- it all reminds me of Out of This World, Heart of Darkness, AND a yoshi game lol- so again camera focus, and positioning are my main points but this is jus a feedback from a rando- this is definitely gunna be on my radar, hope i didnt come off as pretentious or anything, this is all just my opinion and i cant wait to see more : )
